    "Numbers to Ruth_": "Schulchan Aruch, par. 1. c. 580.\nsect. 2.\nft286 --  Apud Hottinger. Smegma Oriental. l. 1. c. 8. p. 457.\nft287 --  See a Journal from Cairo to Mount Sinai, 1722. p. 42,\n2. Time of starting \u2013 10:11, Time in day marches (Deuteronomy l:2)=== eleven days. Time in resting at Kibroth (II: 20) = thirty days. Time in resting at Hazeroth (12:14-15) =seven days. Time total forty-eight days at least, probably more.\n2. The second great breach of the covenant, God's threat of destruction, the intercession of Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]`, the mixed pardon and penalty, 14:1-35.\n2. What the substance, appeal and application of the first oration?",
